Description: Handle of pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp?
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.80, 8. Similar stamps, with or without an extra letter, lambda or upsilon, are in Athens, National Museum and from Corinth and Histria. Virginia Grace (archive notes) suggest thar they may belong to the North Greek Parmeniskos group.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1446)
